## 3. Styling with Tailwind CSS

### Design Tokens — Use Them Religiously

Tailwind v4 uses a CSS-first configuration model. There is **no `tailwind.config.ts`**. All customization lives in your global CSS file via `@theme`.

```css
/* styles/globals.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  /* --- Colors (semantic tokens via CSS variables) --- */
  --color-border: hsl(var(--border));
  --color-background: hsl(var(--background));
  --color-foreground: hsl(var(--foreground));

  --color-primary: hsl(var(--primary));
  --color-primary-foreground: hsl(var(--primary-foreground));

  --color-muted: hsl(var(--muted));
  --color-muted-foreground: hsl(var(--muted-foreground));

  --color-accent: hsl(var(--accent));
  --color-accent-foreground: hsl(var(--accent-foreground));

  --color-destructive: hsl(var(--destructive));
  --color-destructive-foreground: hsl(var(--destructive-foreground));

  --color-card: hsl(var(--card));
  --color-card-foreground: hsl(var(--card-foreground));

  --color-popover: hsl(var(--popover));
  --color-popover-foreground: hsl(var(--popover-foreground));

  /* --- Border Radius --- */
  --radius-lg: var(--radius);
  --radius-md: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
  --radius-sm: calc(var(--radius) - 4px);

  /* --- Custom Spacing (only if you need beyond the default scale) --- */
  /* --spacing-18: 4.5rem; */

  /* --- Fonts --- */
  --font-sans: var(--font-geist-sans), ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-mono: var(--font-geist-mono), ui-monospace, monospace;
}

/* Light/dark mode CSS variable definitions */
:root {
  --background: 0 0% 100%;
  --foreground: 0 0% 3.9%;
  --primary: 0 0% 9%;
  --primary-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  /* ... full token set ... */
  --radius: 0.625rem;
}

.dark {
  --background: 0 0% 3.9%;
  --foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --primary: 0 0% 98%;
  --primary-foreground: 0 0% 9%;
  /* ... full dark token set ... */
}
```

### Tailwind v4 Key Differences — Know These

- **No `tailwind.config.ts`.** All configuration via `@theme` in CSS.
- **`@theme` defines design tokens** that become Tailwind utilities automatically. `--color-primary: ...` generates `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, etc.
- **`@import "tailwindcss"`** replaces the old `@tailwind base/components/utilities` directives.
- **Automatic content detection.** No `content: [...]` config needed — Tailwind v4 scans your project automatically.
- **CSS-native `@theme inline`** can be used to define tokens that don’t generate utility classes (internal-only variables).
- **New default color palette.** Tailwind v4 uses OKLCH colors by default. When using shadcn’s HSL-based tokens, define them explicitly in `@theme`.

### Rules

- **No inline `style={{}}`.** Everything through Tailwind or CSS variables.
- **No arbitrary values like `w-[347px]`.** If a spacing/size isn’t in your scale, add it to `@theme`.
- **Use `cn()` for conditional classes.** Never string concatenation.

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<div className={cn(
  "rounded-lg border bg-card p-6 transition-all duration-200",
  isActive && "ring-2 ring-primary/20 shadow-md",
  className
)} />
```

- **Responsive design is mandatory.** Mobile-first: start with base, layer `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`.
- **Dark mode from day one.** Use semantic color tokens (not `bg-white`/`bg-gray-900`). shadcn handles this via CSS variables defined in `:root` / `.dark`.
- **Extend via `@theme`, not arbitrary values.** If you need a custom token more than once, add it to `@theme` so it’s a first-class utility.

