## 4. Delightful Interactions & Animation

### Motion Principles

- **Purposeful.** Every animation communicates something — entrance, feedback, spatial relationship.
- **Fast.** Most transitions: `150ms–300ms`. Easing: `easeOut` for entrances, `easeIn` for exits, spring for playful interactions.
- **Subtle.** If the user consciously notices the animation, it’s probably too much.
- **Consistent.** Use shared motion presets — never ad-hoc duration/easing values scattered across components.

### Framer Motion Setup

Use `framer-motion` as the primary animation library. Tailwind transitions are acceptable only for trivial hover/focus states. Anything involving enter/exit, layout shifts, gestures, or orchestration must use Framer Motion.

#### Shared Motion Presets

Define once in `lib/motion.ts`. Import everywhere. Never hardcode duration/easing in components.

```tsx
// lib/motion.ts
import { type Variants, type Transition } from "framer-motion";

// --- Transitions ---
export const transition = {
  fast: { duration: 0.15, ease: "easeOut" } satisfies Transition,
  base: { duration: 0.25, ease: [0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1] } satisfies Transition,
  slow: { duration: 0.4, ease: [0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1] } satisfies Transition,
  spring: { type: "spring", stiffness: 350, damping: 30 } satisfies Transition,
  springBouncy: { type: "spring", stiffness: 400, damping: 17 } satisfies Transition,
};

// --- Variant Presets ---
export const fadeIn: Variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, transition: transition.base },
  exit: { opacity: 0, transition: transition.fast },
};

export const fadeUp: Variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 12 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: transition.base },
  exit: { opacity: 0, y: -8, transition: transition.fast },
};

export const fadeDown: Variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: -12 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: transition.base },
};

export const scaleIn: Variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, scale: 0.95 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, scale: 1, transition: transition.spring },
  exit: { opacity: 0, scale: 0.97, transition: transition.fast },
};

export const slideInRight: Variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, x: 20 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, x: 0, transition: transition.base },
  exit: { opacity: 0, x: -10, transition: transition.fast },
};

// --- Stagger Container ---
export const stagger = (staggerDelay = 0.05): Variants => ({
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  visible: {
    opacity: 1,
    transition: { staggerChildren: staggerDelay, delayChildren: 0.05 },
  },
});

// --- Reduced Motion Helper ---
export const reducedMotion: Variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, transition: { duration: 0.01 } },
};
```

#### Reusable Motion Wrapper Component

```tsx
// components/shared/motion-wrapper.tsx
"use client";

import { motion, type Variants, AnimatePresence } from "framer-motion";
import { fadeUp, reducedMotion } from "@/lib/motion";

interface MotionWrapperProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  variants?: Variants;
  className?: string;
  delay?: number;
  as?: keyof typeof motion;  // "div" | "section" | "ul" | "li" etc.
}

export function MotionWrapper({
  children,
  variants = fadeUp,
  className,
  delay = 0,
  as = "div",
}: MotionWrapperProps) {
  const Component = motion[as];

  return (
    <Component
      variants={variants}
      initial="hidden"
      animate="visible"
      exit="exit"
      className={className}
      custom={delay}
      // Respect prefers-reduced-motion at the component level
      {...(typeof window !== "undefined" &&
        window.matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches && {
          variants: reducedMotion,
        })}
    >
      {children}
    </Component>
  );
}
```

### Standard Animation Patterns

```tsx
// --- Page / Section Entrance ---
<motion.div variants={fadeUp} initial="hidden" animate="visible">
  <PageContent />
</motion.div>

// --- Staggered List ---
<motion.ul variants={stagger(0.06)} initial="hidden" animate="visible">
  {items.map((item) => (
    <motion.li key={item.id} variants={fadeUp}>
      <ItemCard item={item} />
    </motion.li>
  ))}
</motion.ul>

// --- Enter/Exit (Conditional Rendering) ---
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  {isOpen && (
    <motion.div
      key="panel"
      variants={scaleIn}
      initial="hidden"
      animate="visible"
      exit="exit"
    >
      <PanelContent />
    </motion.div>
  )}
</AnimatePresence>

// --- Layout Animations (Reordering, Expanding) ---
<motion.div layout layoutId={`card-${item.id}`} transition={transition.spring}>
  <Card />
</motion.div>

// --- Hover & Tap (Gestural Micro-Interactions) ---
<motion.button
  whileHover={{ scale: 1.02, y: -1 }}
  whileTap={{ scale: 0.98 }}
  transition={transition.spring}
>
  Click me
</motion.button>

// --- Skeleton → Content Crossfade ---
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  {isLoading ? (
    <motion.div key="skeleton" variants={fadeIn} initial="hidden" animate="visible" exit="exit">
      <Skeleton />
    </motion.div>
  ) : (
    <motion.div key="content" variants={fadeUp} initial="hidden" animate="visible" exit="exit">
      <ActualContent />
    </motion.div>
  )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

### When to Use Tailwind vs Framer Motion

|Use Tailwind transitions for…|Use Framer Motion for…                                          |
|-----------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
|Hover color/bg shifts        |Enter / exit animations                                         |
|Focus ring appearance        |Staggered list reveals                                          |
|Simple opacity on hover      |Layout animations (reorder, expand)                             |
|Cursor/pointer changes       |Shared layout transitions (`layoutId`)                          |
|                             |Gesture-based interactions (drag, tap, hover with physics)      |
|                             |Orchestrated sequences                                          |
|                             |Scroll-triggered animations                                     |
|                             |Any animation with `AnimatePresence` (conditional mount/unmount)|

### Interaction Signatures

- **Loading states:** Crossfade from skeleton to content using `AnimatePresence mode="wait"`. Spinners only for inline actions (button submissions).
- **Hover states:** Every clickable element has a visible hover state. Cards use `whileHover={{ y: -2, shadow }}`. Buttons use `whileTap={{ scale: 0.98 }}`.
- **Focus states:** Visible, accessible focus rings using `focus-visible:ring-2 ring-ring ring-offset-2` (Tailwind — no Framer needed).
- **Empty states:** Beautiful, helpful illustrations that `fadeUp` into view with a clear CTA. Never just “No data.”
- **Toasts for feedback:** Use `sonner` (already in shadcn). Success = subtle. Error = prominent. Always auto-dismiss success toasts.
- **Optimistic updates:** For mutations, update UI immediately with layout animations for seamless visual continuity.
- **Page transitions:** Use `AnimatePresence` with `mode="wait"` in layouts for smooth route-level transitions.

### Micro-Interactions Checklist

- [ ] Buttons show loading spinner with `AnimatePresence` crossfade + disabled state during async operations
- [ ] Form inputs show validation state with smooth color transitions (Tailwind `transition-colors`)
- [ ] Lists animate items in with `stagger()` + `fadeUp` variants
- [ ] Conditional UI uses `AnimatePresence` — nothing pops in/out without a transition
- [ ] Cards and interactive surfaces use `whileHover` / `whileTap` for physicality
- [ ] Modals/dialogs use `scaleIn` variants with backdrop `fadeIn`
- [ ] Reorderable items use `layout` prop for smooth position changes
- [ ] Shared elements across views use `layoutId` for visual continuity
- [ ] Tooltips use `fadeIn` with a 200ms delay via `transition={{ delay: 0.2 }}`
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` is respected — decorative animations are suppressed

