## 10. Error Handling

- **Error boundaries** at the page and feature level. Use `error.tsx` in App Router.
- **Graceful degradation.** If a non-critical feature fails, the page still works.
- **User-friendly messages.** Never show raw error objects, stack traces, or technical jargon to users.
- **Log structurally.** Errors sent to logging include: message, component, user context, timestamp.

```tsx
// app/dashboard/error.tsx
"use client";

export default function DashboardError({ error, reset }: { error: Error; reset: () => void }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 py-20">
      <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">Something went wrong</h2>
      <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">We couldn't load your dashboard. Please try again.</p>
      <Button onClick={reset} variant="outline">Try again</Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

